# Auto-deploy after every change

After completing **any** code edit to the ClipSmart site, always finish the session by:

1. Running `git add -A`
2. Writing the commit message to a temp file (`commit_msg.txt`) — **never use heredoc syntax**, this is a PowerShell shell
3. Committing with `git commit -F commit_msg.txt`
4. Deleting the temp file
5. Running `git push`

This ensures Netlify picks up every change automatically without the user having to ask.

## Example (PowerShell-safe)

```powershell
git add -A
Set-Content -Path commit_msg.txt -Value "feat: describe what changed"
git commit -F commit_msg.txt
Remove-Item commit_msg.txt
git push
```

Never skip this step after making changes to src/, public/, or any config file.
